 Review comment:
   @rok A SparseTensorCOO consists of the indices and the data, so it consists of three buffers (the one is its metadata).  Likewise, a SparseTensorCSR consists of the indices, the indptr, and the data, so it consists of four buffers.
   
   Therefore, we should manage the number of COO and CSR separately.

